show.description: Akshat Pathak, the troubled son of powerful MLA Nandani Pathak, is trapped beneath a legacy of emotional abuse and political expectations. But everything changes when he crosses paths with Saksharta, a fierce and self-made orphan from a foster home whose only family is her younger brother, Anay. Their connection sparks a series of confrontations — with class, love, identity, and the rotten roots of systemic power. As secrets unravel, Saksharta discovers her true lineage — she is the long-lost daughter of political tycoon Vishwas Singh, making her the unexpected heiress in a game ruled by lies and leverage. What begins as schoolyard taunts and broken hearts escalates into campus campaigns, leaked scandals, public takedowns, and courtroom showdowns. Former lovers turn enemies, and enemies become allies. With Akshat ultimately choosing truth over blood and exposing his own mother’s corruption, he and Saksharta take a stand — not just for themselves, but for a generation fighting to be heard.
